{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddc91ec57-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s190g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"190g"},"text":"§ 190g.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Nonconsideration of certain private bills and resolutions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No private bill or resolution (including so-called omnibus claims or pension bills), and no amendment to any bill or resolution, authorizing or directing (1) the payment of money for property damages, for personal injuries or death for which suit may be instituted under the Federal Tort Claims Act, or for a pension (other than to carry out a provision of law or treaty stipulation); (2) the construction of a bridge across a navigable stream; or (3) the correction of a military or naval record, shall be received or considered in either the Senate ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002018"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002018"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See Partial Repeal note below."}],"tail":" or the House of Representatives."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddc91ec58-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch753"},"text":"Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 753","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 131, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/831"},"text":"60 Stat. 831","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddc91ec59-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddc91ec5a-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddc91ec5b-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Tort Claims Act, referred to in text, is title IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch753"},"text":"act Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 753","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/842"},"text":"60 Stat. 842","children":[],"tail":", which was classified principally to chapter 20 (§§ 921, 922, 931–934, 941–946) of former Title 28, Judicial Code and Judiciary. Title IV of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-08-02"},"text":"Aug. 2, 1946","children":[],"tail":", was substantially repealed and reenacted as sections 1346(b) and 2671 et seq. of Title 28, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"act June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/992"},"text":"62 Stat. 992","children":[],"tail":", the first section of which enacted Title 28. For complete classification of title IV to the Code, see Tables. For distribution of former sections of Title 28 into the revised Title 28, see Table at the beginning of Title 28."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddc94354c-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"iddc94354d-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1947","children":[],"tail":", see section 142 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch753/tI"},"text":"act Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 753, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/834"},"text":"60 Stat. 834","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc94354e-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Partial Repeal","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 2(a), S. Res. 274, Ninety-sixth Congress, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1979","children":[],"tail":", provided in part that this section, insofar as it relates to the Senate, is repealed. See Standing Rules of the Senate."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
